caption.center: DORIS COULTER, EMPLOYEE, CLAIMANT v. WEYERHAEUSER, SELF-INSURED EMPLOYER,

court.center: Before the Arkansas Workers' Compensation Commission

opinion.panel: Upon review before the FULL COMMISSION in Little Rock, Pulaski County, Arkansas.
opinion.attorneys:
Claimant represented by the HONORABLE KENNETH A. OLSEN, Attorney at Law, Little Rock, Arkansas.
Respondents represented by the HONORABLE JUDY WILBER, Attorney at Law, Little Rock, Arkansas.
opinion.opinion_text:
ORDER In the above-styled matter, the respondent has filed a Motion ForExtension of Time To File Brief. The respondent states that the parties are engaging in settlement negotiations, and that the claimant does not object to the respondent's request.
Therefore, we grant the respondent's motion.
IT IS SO ORDERED.
________________________________ ELDON F. COFFMAN, Chairman
____________________________________________________ MIKE WILSON, Commissioner
________________________________ SHELBY W. TURNER, Commissioner
